RABAT, Morocco, July 4, 2022/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            His Majesty King Mohammed VI has sent a congratulatory message to the President of the United States of America, HEM. Joseph Robinette Biden, on the occasion of his country's Independence Day.


                                HM the King further reiterates Morocco's "unshakable resolve to strengthen dialogue, consultation and coordination" with the United States in international forums
                            

In this message, the Sovereign expresses, on behalf of Himself and of the Moroccan people, His warmest congratulations to President Biden and His wishes for more progress and prosperity to the American people.

"I should like you to know, Mr. President, how much I value the time-honored relations between the Kingdom of Morocco and the United States of America, which are grounded in close friendship, mutual esteem and active solidarity," says HM the King.

"I very much look forward to continuing to work with you to strengthen our ties and promote our strategic partnership, thus fulfilling our ambitions as well as the aspirations of our peoples," the Sovereign continues. HM the King further reiterates Morocco's "unshakable resolve to strengthen dialogue, consultation and coordination" with the United States in international forums, regarding all matters of common concern.

"In this way, we would serve our countriesâ€™ shared interests and contribute to preserving peace, security and stability in the world," the Sovereign points out.